{"hadithnumber": "3714", "text": "Hanzalah narrated that he heard Tawus say:\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'Ruqba is not permissible. Whoever is given something on the basis of Ruqba, it is part of his estate"}
{"hadithnumber": "3715", "text": "Sufyan narrated from Ibn Abi Najih, from Tawus, from Zaid bin Thabit, who said:\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'Umra (a gift given for life) is part of the estate"}
{"hadithnumber": "3716", "text": "Sufyan narrated from Ibn Tawus, from his father, from Hujr Al-Madari, from Zaid, who said:\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'Umra (a gift given for life) is for the heir"}
{"hadithnumber": "3717", "text": "Ma'mar narrated from Ibn Tawus, from his father, from Hujr Al-Madari, from Zaid bin Thabit, from Prophet, who said:\"'Umra (a gift given for life) is permissible"}
{"hadithnumber": "3718", "text": "Ma'mar narrated from 'Amr bin Dinar, from Tawus, from Zaid bin Thabit, that the Prophet said:\"'Umra (a gift given for life) belongs to the heir"}
{"hadithnumber": "3719", "text": "(A different chain) from Ma'mar who said:\"I heard 'Amr bin Dinar, narrating from Tawus, from Hujr Al-Madari, from Zaid bin Thabit, that the Messenger of Allah said: \"'Umra (a gift given for life) belongs to the heir.\" And Allah knows best"}
{"hadithnumber": "3720", "text": "It was narrated from Zaid bin Thabit that the Prophet said:\"'Umra (a gift given for life) belongs to the heir"}
{"hadithnumber": "3721", "text": "It was narrated from Zaid bin Thabit that the Messenger of Allah said:\"'Umra (a gift given for life) belongs to the heir"}
{"hadithnumber": "3722", "text": "It was narrated from Zaid bin Thabit that the Prophet ruled that 'Umra (a gift given for life) belongs to the heir"}
{"hadithnumber": "3722.2", "text": "It was narrated from Zaid bin Thabit that the Prophet ruled that 'Umra (a gift given for life) belongs to the heir"}
{"hadithnumber": "3723", "text": "It was narrated that Zaid bin Thabit said:The Messenger of Allah said: \"Whoever gives a life-long gift, it belongs to the one to whom he gave it, both during his life and after his death. And do not give things on the basis of Ruqba, for whoever is given something on the basis of Ruqba, it becomes part of his estate"}
{"hadithnumber": "3724", "text": "It was narrated from 'Abdullah bin 'Abbas that the Prophet said:\"'Umra is permissible"}
{"hadithnumber": "3725", "text": "It was narrated from Ibn 'Abbas that the Prophet said:\"Indeed 'Umra is permissible"}
{"hadithnumber": "3726", "text": "It was narrated from Tawus that the Messenger of Allah made 'Umra and Ruqba binding"}
{"hadithnumber": "3727", "text": "Malik bin Dinar narrated from 'Ata', from Jabir that the Messenger of Allah addressed them one day and said:\"'Umra is permissible"}
